        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "I ran into a small issue with Zend_Loader_PluginLoader, where I have it lazy load some event listeners. The class of one of the listeners was already loaded, and Zend_Loader_PluginLoader didn't find it. Although it's certainly true that Zend_Loader_PluginLoader isn't needed for classes that are already loaded, and in almost all cases I've encountered this hasn't come up, it seems worth a call to class_exists just in case. I wrote a snippet to deal with this which I included below.\r\n\r\nclass TheOkPhatzby_Loader_PluginLoader extends Zend_Loader_PluginLoader {\r\n\t\r\n    public function load($name, $throwExceptions = true)\r\n    {\r\n        if(class_exists($name, false)){\r\n            return $name;\r\n        }\r\n        return parent::load($name, $throwExceptions);\r\n    }\t\r\n\t\r\n}"
        },
